  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "No new keys today. The whole job is an even tempo held over a long stretch - the way a paragraph reads when nothing in it stumbles. Three words, each repeated at one steady pace."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Hands on the home row, thumbs over the space bar, eyes up. Repeat each word without rushing. When the pace drifts, count it back: one, two, three, four."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "metronome",
      "title": "Even hands",
      "text": "A long paragraph is a test of stamina, not sprinting. Keep the same gap between keystrokes from the first word to the last. The work that holds its tempo is the work that gets finished on time."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "evening evening evening evening evening",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Rhythm: evening",
      "hint": "Repeat at one tempo: evening - evening - evening. Hold the gaps equal."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "keyboard keyboard keyboard keyboard",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Rhythm: keyboard",
      "hint": "Repeat steadily, no jerks: keyboard - keyboard - keyboard."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "feature feature feature feature",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: feature",
      "hint": "Repeat evenly: feature - feature - feature. Do not speed up at the end."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Let the hand take each word in one motion, the way you read a word you have written a thousand times. Even repetition is how the movement becomes automatic - and the automatic hand is the one that lasts a full page."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "Loosen your shoulders and wrists, picture the metronome, and let the rhythm carry you. Steady beats fast.",
      "by": "Eleanor Hayes, editor"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "All three done? Open the trainer below and take one clean run at the full lesson text. That run saves your progress and unlocks the next lesson."
    }
  ],
  "character_tips": {
    "anna": "Multi-sentence rhythm is real-world writing speed. Hold the tempo.",
